                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem>Ἀριστω<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg>Ἀρίστω<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></rdg>
                        <rdg><note>or</note> Ἀριστώ<supplied reason="lost">νυμος</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristô<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristo<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristo<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This might be a base, the upper moulding of which would be totally erased. If so, a name and father's name should be read and the base would rather be 
               funerary for the lack of attachment holes on the upper face. Yet, this point is not quite sure because of the rear being broken off.</p>
            </div></body>
